It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that has only been minimally decorated.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and bed. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom-make a wardrobe.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the chimney, their bodies completely dried up :(
Get ready for the masonry work next week
Satisfied with the small niche next to it
Install the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing yet 😈)
Ha ha, check out what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the cute little vent we added to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep has installed both the chimney cap and the chimney cover. The white-shouldered starlings that like to nest in chimneys should be safer now 🪺
The plasterer has finished their work. We'll lay the flooring tomorrow!
The cork underlayment has been laid, and we made a accessory for the vacuum cleaner using a toilet paper roll to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the flooring has been prepared and is ready to start laying. Let's have a cup of tea and rest for a while.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because we needed to make cuts around the door frame to ensure a seamless connection with the corridor (which is also being floored). It was quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me
Finally finished, but it's all messed up! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
There's still the corridor floor and baseboards left. The renovation workers come a month later, so we can only live in a makeshift way now, with only bare gypsum boards in the room.
Last night I did a simple DIY job, using a tenon saw and chisel to cut off part of the bottom of the door frame, so that the floor can fit perfectly underneath.
The cork underlayment in the corridor is also laid out now
We finished laying the corridor floor yesterday! This morning at 5 a.m., I went to Heathrow Airport to pick up the first package, had a nap, and now finally can start installing the baseboards in the corridor. Fill the joints after the glue dries.
